# Sync skills configuration

Whenever a new skill is installed, **update `skills.json` in the same change set** so the configuration stays versioned and can be restored with `upgrade-agent-skills`.

## Add or update entries

- After installing a skill from a GitHub URL or `owner/repo@skill`, open `skills.json` and update `install[]`.
- If the source already has an entry, add the new skill name to its `skills` array.
- If the source does not exist yet, add a new object such as `{ "source": "<url or repo>", "skills": ["<skill-name>"] }`.
- If the source is configured to install the whole repo, omit the `skills` field.
- Use the same source style as existing entries, for example `https://github.com/owner/repo`.

## Preserve structure

- Follow the existing structure: `source` plus `skills` when needed.
- Per-entry options such as `agents`, `global`, or `yes` are optional.
- Top-level `defaults` apply unless an entry overrides them.

## Sort after every edit

- After any edit to `skills.json`, run `jq`.
- Keep JSON indentation at **4 spaces**.
- Sort `install[]` by `.source`.
- If an entry has `skills`, sort that array too.

```sh
jq --indent 4 '.install |= (sort_by(.source) | map(if has("skills") then .skills |= sort else . end))' skills.json
```

## Do not remove entries

- Do not remove existing skills or sources unless the user explicitly asks to uninstall or clean up.

## File and format

- File: **`skills.json`** at the repo root (e.g. `~/.local/share/chezmoi/skills.json`).
- Format: `install` is an array of `{ "source": "...", "skills": ["a", "b"] }` objects.
- Some entries may contain only `source` when the whole repo should be installed.

## Reminder

- If the user asks to add or install a skill and you run `npx skills add`, also update `skills.json`.
- Finish by running the `jq` sort step before considering the task complete.

For example, when running:

```sh
npx skills add https://github.com/vercel-labs/agent-skills --skill web-design-guidelines
```

also make sure that `skills.json` contains an entry for `https://github.com/vercel-labs/skills` with `"web-design-guidelines"` listed in its `skills` array, and keep both the `install` list and `skills` arrays sorted.

## Commit message guidelines

When a change involves `skills.json`, the commit message should make this explicit so that it is easy to track skill configuration changes in history.

Recommended patterns:

- `chore(skills): Add <skill-name> skill`
- `chore(skills): Add <skill-name-1> and <skill-name-2> skills`
- `chore(skills): Add skills and update sync rule`
- `docs(skills): Clarify agent-skills sync workflow`

Rules of thumb:

- Use the `skills` scope for commits that touch `skills.json` and/or `.cursor/rules/agent-skills-sync.mdc`.
- When adding multiple skills in one commit, prefer a plural description such as `Add multiple skills` or mention the most important ones.
- When you change both the rule file and `skills.json`, prefer a message that reflects both, for example `chore(skills): Add skills and update sync rule`.
